01:37.880 --> 01:40.491
♪ I'LL BE READY

01:41.013 --> 01:44.016
♪ FOREVER AND ALWAYS ♪

01:44.147 --> 01:47.107
♪ I'M ALWAYS HERE

02:02.470 --> 02:04.820
[LIVELY MUSIC]

03:00.223 --> 03:02.269
-HOBIE: HEY, BRENDA, WAIT UP!

03:02.399 --> 03:04.053
BRENDA!

03:04.184 --> 03:06.011
BRENDA, SLOW DOWN!

03:07.187 --> 03:08.971
BRENDA, WAIT UP!

03:09.101 --> 03:12.670
[LIVELY MUSIC]

03:25.074 --> 03:26.293
BRENDA, WAIT UP!

03:26.423 --> 03:27.468
-WHOA!

03:28.164 --> 03:29.557
-HOBIE: BRENDA,
WHERE ARE YOU GOING?

03:29.687 --> 03:31.036
-BRENDA: WHOA!

03:31.167 --> 03:34.518
[FRANTIC MUSIC]

03:56.584 --> 04:00.544
[COUGHING]

04:09.292 --> 04:10.380
-HOBIE: CAN YOU BREATHE?

04:12.382 --> 04:14.123
[COUGHING]

04:14.254 --> 04:15.690
PUSH ON MY HAND.

04:15.820 --> 04:17.344
[COUGHING]

04:18.822 --> 04:20.172
SQUEEZE MY HAND.

04:20.303 --> 04:22.087
-HOBIE, I'M ALRIGHT.

04:24.307 --> 04:25.700
YOU BETTER NOT TRY TO KISS ME.

04:25.830 --> 04:27.310
-KISS YOU?

04:27.441 --> 04:29.617
I WAS JUST TRYING TO
MAKE SURE YOU WERE OKAY.

04:30.444 --> 04:32.359
COULD HAVE BROKEN YOUR
NECK OR SOMETHING.

04:32.489 --> 04:34.230
[EVERYONE LAUGHING]

04:34.361 --> 04:37.451
-OKAY, SO IT'S ME, HER, AND
THE DOG IN THE SLEEPING BAG,

04:37.581 --> 04:39.148
IT'S POURING RAIN--

04:39.279 --> 04:41.063
-DON: MITCH, MITCH, COME
SEE WHAT THE CAT DRAGGED IN.

04:41.193 --> 04:43.413
-BRODY, MAN, HIYA!

04:43.544 --> 04:45.546
-HOW YOU DOIN', LIEUTENANT?

04:45.676 --> 04:46.764
GOOD TO SEE YOU, MAN.

04:46.895 --> 04:48.070
-CAN I HAVE YOUR AUTOGRAPH?

04:48.200 --> 04:49.114
MIND YOU, IT'S NOT
EVERY DAY WE GET

04:49.245 --> 04:50.290
AN INTERNATIONAL CELEBRITY HERE.

04:50.420 --> 04:51.813
-LISTEN TO YOU.

04:51.943 --> 04:53.075
-I HOPE HE DOESN'T
WANT HIS OLD JOB BACK.

04:53.205 --> 04:54.772
-OH.
-HEY, WHAT'S A MATTER?

04:54.903 --> 04:56.600
A GUY CAN'T COME BACK
AND VISIT A FEW OF HIS BUDS?

04:57.645 --> 04:59.211
SO, I MISS YA, BIG LUG.

04:59.342 --> 05:02.084
-LANE! HEY!

05:02.214 --> 05:02.998
-LANE: HI.

05:03.128 --> 05:04.216
[SHAUNI LAUGHING]

05:04.347 --> 05:06.349
-SHAUNI: I AM SO PROUD OF YOU.

05:06.480 --> 05:09.265
THIS MAN RISKED HIS LIFE
TO SAVE BABY HARP SEALS.

05:09.787 --> 05:10.875
IT WAS VERY HEROIC.

05:11.006 --> 05:13.095
-SINKING A SHIP,
THAT'S HEROIC.

05:13.225 --> 05:15.358
-THIS WAS A SHIP THAT
WAS CARRYING HUNTERS OUT

05:15.489 --> 05:17.012
TO KILL DEFENSELESS ANIMALS.

05:18.927 --> 05:20.668
-I DON'T NEED YOU
TO DEFEND ME, SHAUNI.

05:20.798 --> 05:22.496
I HAVE AN ATTORNEY
THAT DOES THAT.

05:22.626 --> 05:25.847
AND, BEN, I'M NOT ASKING YOU
TO APPROVE OF OUR TACTICS,

05:25.977 --> 05:27.109
JUST THE RESULTS.

05:27.239 --> 05:28.980
IF IT WEREN'T FOR GREENFORCE--

05:29.111 --> 05:30.417
-YOU WOULDN'T HAVE MADE THE
COVER OF "NEWSWEEK" MAGAZINE.

05:31.200 --> 05:34.116
NOT TO MENTION 60 DAYS
IN AN ALASKAN JAIL.

05:34.638 --> 05:36.901
-YEAH, MORE LIKE A
MAXIMUM SECURITY IGLOO.

05:37.032 --> 05:38.903
[EVERYONE LAUGHING]

05:39.034 --> 05:42.690
[UPBEAT MUSIC]

06:03.188 --> 06:06.931
-♪ FLYING DOWN THE HIGHWAY

06:07.628 --> 06:10.108
♪ UNDER THE SUN

06:10.892 --> 06:14.417
♪ I'M GONNA PLAY THE WHOLE DAY ♪

06:15.331 --> 06:17.638
♪ GONNA HAVE SOME FUN

06:18.421 --> 06:22.251
♪ I GOT PLENTY OF REASONS

06:23.121 --> 06:25.385
♪ TO CHASE MY DREAM

06:26.211 --> 06:29.127
♪ THE GIRLS HERE IN CALIFORNIA ♪

06:29.258 --> 06:31.826
♪ ARE WHAT I MEAN

06:36.918 --> 06:38.441
♪ IT'S A WONDERFUL DAY

06:44.708 --> 06:47.494
♪ IT'S A WONDERFUL DAY

06:50.671 --> 06:52.150
-LANE: WHAT DO YOU THINK
OF OUR TACTICS, MITCH?

06:52.281 --> 06:53.413
DO YOU SEE GREENFORCE
AS A BUNCH OF

06:53.543 --> 06:55.371
WILD-EYED ECO-TERRORISTS?

06:55.502 --> 06:57.852
-I DON'T KNOW, I
HAVEN'T DECIDED YET.

06:58.766 --> 07:00.420
-YOU KNOW, THERE'S
REALLY NOT MUCH DIFFERENCE

07:00.550 --> 07:02.073
BETWEEN WHAT I DO NOW AND
WHAT I DID AS A LIFEGUARD.

07:02.683 --> 07:04.336
IT'S ALL ABOUT PREVENTION.

07:04.467 --> 07:06.469
WE ACT TO STOP THE NEXT
DISASTER BEFORE IT HAPPENS

07:06.600 --> 07:08.297
JUST LIKE YOU DO.

07:08.428 --> 07:10.212
-WAIT A MINUTE, I'VE NEVER
BEEN ARRESTED FOR MAKING A SAVE.

07:10.995 --> 07:12.170
IT'S NOT THE SAME THING.

07:13.911 --> 07:15.565
-YEAH, BUT WHAT'S
THE ALTERNATIVE?

07:15.696 --> 07:18.481
I TRIED WORKING THROUGH THE
SYSTEM, I WROTE LETTERS,

07:18.612 --> 07:20.265
I MARCHED IN DEMONSTRATIONS,

07:20.396 --> 07:22.703
I SPENT SIX MONTHS IN
WASHINGTON LOBBYING CONGRESS.

07:23.268 --> 07:24.748
MITCH, THE SYSTEM DOES NOT WORK,

07:24.879 --> 07:27.229
AT LEAST NOT FAST ENOUGH
FOR ME, OR THE PLANET.

07:27.359 --> 07:28.970
AT THE PRESENT RATE WE'RE
DESTROYING THE OZONE LAYER--

07:29.100 --> 07:30.928
-LANE, I ADMIRE WHAT
YOU'RE TRYING TO DO,

07:31.059 --> 07:33.365
I JUST DON'T AGREE WITH THE
WAY YOU GO ABOUT DOING IT.

07:33.975 --> 07:35.846
-DOES THAT MEAN I
SHOULDN'T ASK FOR YOUR HELP?

07:35.977 --> 07:37.848
[DOOR BANGING]
-NOT NECESSARILY.

07:44.855 --> 07:45.987
[DOORS BANGING]

07:46.944 --> 07:48.468
WHAT KIND OF HELP ARE
YOU TALKING ABOUT?

07:49.033 --> 07:51.253
-ABOUT A MONTH AGO I
WAS CONTACTED BY SOMEONE

07:51.383 --> 07:53.037
ON THE INSIDE OF
TRANSICON INDUSTRIES.

07:53.168 --> 07:54.474
YOU'VE PROBABLY HEARD OF THEM,

07:54.604 --> 07:55.431
THEY'RE A BIG
PLASTICS MANUFACTURER.

07:55.562 --> 07:57.259
-YEAH.

07:57.389 --> 07:59.827
-LANE: ANYWAY, THIS GUY'S
PREPARED TO BLOW THE WHISTLE

07:59.957 --> 08:01.698
ON THEIR ENTIRE WASTE
MANAGEMENT OPERATION.

08:01.829 --> 08:03.395
SAYS THAT THEY'VE GOTTEN
AWAY WITH HUNDREDS

08:03.526 --> 08:04.875
OF ILLEGAL DUMPINGS.

08:05.006 --> 08:06.529
HE'S GOT ACCESS TO DOCUMENTS,

08:06.660 --> 08:07.530
ALL WE GOT TO DO IS GET
IN THERE AND GET THEM OUT.

08:09.314 --> 08:10.794
-YOU MEAN STEAL THEM.

08:11.403 --> 08:12.753
-IN ORDER TO SHUT
DOWN A MAJOR POLLUTER?

08:12.883 --> 08:14.276
YEAH, IF THAT'S WHAT IT TAKES.

08:15.059 --> 08:17.192
LOOK, MITCH, I'M NOT ASKING
YOU TO GET DIRECTLY INVOLVED.

08:17.975 --> 08:19.020
NOBODY'S GONNA GET HURT.

08:20.587 --> 08:23.111
-[SIGHS] WELL, WHAT
ARE YOU ASKING ME?

08:24.112 --> 08:26.593
-WELL, I'M JUST NOT 100%
SOLD ON THIS WHISTLE BLOWER.

08:26.723 --> 08:28.377
I'VE ONLY SPOKEN WITH
HIM ON THE PHONE,

08:28.508 --> 08:31.554
AND I WOULDN'T MIND SOME BACKUP
WHEN THIS THING GOES DOWN.

08:34.251 --> 08:35.818
-SORRY, LANE, I CAN'T DO IT.

08:35.950 --> 08:38.039
-MITCH, YOU GOTTA DRAW
THE LINE SOMEWHERE.

08:38.169 --> 08:41.346
-I DO, I DRAW THE LINE
AT BREAKING THE LAW.

08:42.043 --> 08:43.392
[ENGINE REVVING]

08:47.004 --> 08:50.094
[BLUESY MUSIC]

09:17.121 --> 09:18.383
[DOOR OPENING]

09:18.514 --> 09:20.777
YO, HOBSTER, CATCH!

09:21.561 --> 09:22.953
YOU REMEMBER LANE BRODY,

09:23.084 --> 09:25.303
FORMER LIFEGUARD TURNED
ENVIRONMENTAL COMMANDO.

09:25.434 --> 09:26.522
-HOW YOU DOIN', HOBIE?

09:26.653 --> 09:28.045
-HI.
-YEAH, GOOD TO SEE YA.

09:28.176 --> 09:29.699
I HOPE YOU DON'T MIND IF
I JOIN YOU GUYS TONIGHT.

09:30.265 --> 09:31.658
-YOU MEAN AT THE GRAND PRIX?

09:31.788 --> 09:33.485
-OH, YEAH! I USED TO
LOVE THOSE LITTLE CARS.

09:33.616 --> 09:34.617
YOU CAN PRETEND
YOU'RE MARIO ANDRETTI,

09:34.748 --> 09:35.923
WHIP AROUND THOSE TURNS.

09:36.053 --> 09:37.751
-WHEN DID CAPTAIN THORPE CALL?

09:37.881 --> 09:39.361
-ABOUT 10 MINUTES AGO.

09:39.491 --> 09:41.102
-RIGHT, WE'RE GONNA GO
PUT ON SOME SWEATERS,

09:41.232 --> 09:42.451
IT'S KIND OF CHILLY OUTSIDE.

09:42.582 --> 09:43.321
WOULD YOU AH...
-YEAH, I'VE GOT IT.

09:43.452 --> 09:44.627
-THANKS.

09:49.545 --> 09:50.328
[KNOCKING]

09:50.459 --> 09:52.113
-HELLO?
-HI.

09:52.243 --> 09:53.070
-SHAUNI: HEY!
-COME ON IN.

09:53.201 --> 09:54.158
-GREAT.

09:55.769 --> 09:57.727
EDDIE'S STILL BACK EAST
AT THE LIFEGUARD GAMES,

09:57.858 --> 09:59.250
SO I THOUGHT I'D SEE WHAT
YOU GUYS WERE UP TO TONIGHT.

09:59.381 --> 10:01.165
-OH, GREAT, WE'RE GLAD YOU DID.

10:01.296 --> 10:02.253
AT LEAST I AM.

10:03.298 --> 10:05.300
SO HOW IS EDDIE,
ARE YOU GUYS HAPPY?

10:05.430 --> 10:06.344
DO YOU LIKE LIVING TOGETHER?

10:06.475 --> 10:07.694
-YEAH, YEAH, IT'S GREAT.

10:07.824 --> 10:10.435
-YEAH, BUMMER. [LAUGHING]

10:11.219 --> 10:12.307
-HEY, SHAUNI, YOU
WANNA GO TO THE

10:12.437 --> 10:14.004
MALIBU GRAND PRIX WITH US?

10:14.135 --> 10:14.875
-YEAH, SURE, WHY NOT?

10:15.005 --> 10:15.876
-GREAT!

10:16.006 --> 10:16.833
-HEY.

10:16.964 --> 10:18.139
-SHAUNI: HEY.

10:19.531 --> 10:23.405
-BAD NEWS, HOBIE, I JUST
TALKED TO CAPTAIN THORPE,

10:23.971 --> 10:26.277
THERE'S A SPECIAL MEETING AT
COUNTY HEADQUARTERS TONIGHT.

10:26.843 --> 10:28.889
ATTENDANCE IS MANDATORY.

10:30.673 --> 10:31.543
-I KNEW IT.

10:32.675 --> 10:34.068
-I'M SORRY, PAL, BELIEVE ME.

10:34.198 --> 10:35.635
LOOK, WE'LL DO IT
ANOTHER TIME, OKAY?

10:35.765 --> 10:37.245
-THAT'S WHAT YOU ALWAYS SAY.

10:37.375 --> 10:39.116
-HEY, WAIT A MINUTE,
WHO NEEDS YOUR OLD MAN?

10:39.247 --> 10:40.465
WE'LL TAKE YA!

10:40.596 --> 10:41.510
-YOU WILL?

10:41.641 --> 10:42.990
CAN THEY, DAD?

10:44.774 --> 10:45.993
-HOBIE, ARE YOU
SURE YOU'RE UP TO IT,

10:46.123 --> 10:47.429
BECAUSE YOU LOOK
A LITTLE PALE.

10:47.559 --> 10:49.170
MITCH, HE LOOKS A
LITTLE PALE TO ME.

10:49.910 --> 10:52.216
-UH-HUH, I'M OKAY,
COME ON, LET'S GO.

10:54.305 --> 11:00.268
-UH, GO ON, AND BE CAREFUL,
AND HAVE A GREAT TIME, AND UH

11:01.791 --> 11:04.011
DON'T GO TOO FAST
AROUND THOSE TURNS.

11:04.141 --> 11:07.710
[LIVELY MUSIC]

11:20.157 --> 11:22.594
-♪ WELL YOU WORK IN THE CITY

11:23.465 --> 11:25.380
♪ RUSH HOUR EVERY DAY

11:26.294 --> 11:28.165
♪ AND YOU WANT TO DRIVE FASTER

11:29.253 --> 11:30.646
♪ YOU WANT TO GET AWAY

11:32.126 --> 11:33.736
♪ PUT THE PEDAL TO THE FLOOR

11:35.085 --> 11:36.957
♪ FEEL THE WIND IN YOUR HAIR

11:37.827 --> 11:39.263
♪ YOU NEED A LITTLE MORE

11:40.569 --> 11:42.353
♪ WELL IT'S ALL RIGHT THERE

11:43.267 --> 11:44.660
♪ CMON

11:48.795 --> 11:50.231
♪ CMON

11:54.975 --> 11:57.717
♪ I'VE BEEN BIG I'VE BEEN SMALL

11:57.847 --> 12:00.502
♪ I'VE HAD NOTHING
I'VE HAD IT ALL ♪

12:00.632 --> 12:04.245
♪ I GLIMPSED HEAVEN
WHEN I HIT THE WALL ♪

12:08.989 --> 12:11.818
♪ I'VE BEEN BETTER
I'VE BEEN WORSE ♪

12:11.948 --> 12:14.516
♪ I'VE BEEN BLESSED AND
I'VE BEEN CURSED ♪

12:14.646 --> 12:17.606
♪ I GLIMPSED HEAVEN
WHEN I HIT THE WALL ♪

12:21.828 --> 12:23.655
♪ WHEN I HIT THE WALL

12:40.672 --> 12:42.936
[TIRES SCREECHING]
-OH NO!

12:43.066 --> 12:44.285
[RACING MUSIC]

12:53.120 --> 12:54.208
-LANE: HOBIE, WHAT HAPPENED?

12:54.338 --> 12:55.383
ARE YOU HURT?

12:56.471 --> 12:59.387
-[HOBIE MOANING]
-[DISTORTED] HOBIE,
ARE YOU OKAY?

13:00.867 --> 13:02.042
HOBIE?

13:03.347 --> 13:04.958
-ARE YOU OKAY?

13:05.088 --> 13:07.395
[MOANING]

13:09.353 --> 13:11.051
-SHAUNI:
LET'S GET HIM HOME.

13:16.186 --> 13:18.710
-ALL I REMEMBER IS MY
HEAD STARTED SPINNING.

13:19.537 --> 13:21.409
I FELT LIKE I WAS
GONNA THROW UP.

13:22.105 --> 13:25.805
-WELL IT'S NO WONDER, YOU'VE
GOT 104 TEMPERATURE, PAL.

13:26.370 --> 13:27.371
-I'LL RUN HIM A COLD BATH.

13:27.502 --> 13:28.720
-YEAH.

13:28.851 --> 13:30.244
I'M GONNA GET SOME ICE.

13:30.374 --> 13:31.375
WOULD YOU HELP HIM
TAKE HIS CLOTHES OFF?

13:31.506 --> 13:34.074
-YEAH.
-MITCH: OKAY? OKAY.

13:39.514 --> 13:43.126
[FOOTSTEPS STOMPING]

13:46.216 --> 13:48.436
[PHONE RINGING]

13:50.046 --> 13:53.354
YEAH? OH, ACTUALLY,
MRS. NICKMAN, THIS IS
A BAD TIME,

13:53.484 --> 13:55.443
HOBIE'S GOT SOME KIND OF BUG.

13:56.879 --> 13:57.837
SHE DOES?

14:00.404 --> 14:01.579
-HERE WE GO.

14:03.755 --> 14:05.496
-SHAUNI, LET ME SEE SOME LIGHT.

14:05.627 --> 14:06.628
-OKAY.

14:11.676 --> 14:13.417
WHAT IS THAT?
IS THAT A RASH?

14:14.331 --> 14:15.376
-LANE: A SKIN IRRITATION,

14:15.506 --> 14:16.725
HE'S GOT SOME ON
HIS LEG AS WELL.

14:16.856 --> 14:18.292
-SHAUNI: SOME
ON HIS NECK, TOO.

14:19.423 --> 14:20.947
-HOBIE, DO YOU HAVE
ALLERGIES OF ANY KIND?

14:21.991 --> 14:23.514
-NO, I DON'T THINK SO.

14:23.645 --> 14:25.038
-HAVE YOU BEEN SWIMMING TODAY?

14:25.690 --> 14:26.474
-YEAH.

14:26.604 --> 14:27.736
-LANE: WHERE?

14:28.737 --> 14:31.958
-THE LAGOON, MY FRIEND BRENDA
FELL IN, I HAD TO HELP HER.

14:32.610 --> 14:33.960
-I JUST GOT A CALL
FROM BRENDA'S MOM,

14:34.090 --> 14:35.265
LOOKS LIKE BRENDA'S
GOT THE SAME THING.

14:36.223 --> 14:37.224
-CALL HER BACK AND
TELL HER TO GET HER

14:37.354 --> 14:38.878
TO AN EMERGENCY ROOM.

14:39.008 --> 14:40.618
-WHAT?

14:40.749 --> 14:42.359
-IT'S NOT THE FLU, MITCH,
IT'S CHEMICAL POISONING.

14:42.490 --> 14:43.926
THEY HAVE BEEN EXPOSED TO
A HIGHLY TOXIC SUBSTANCE.

14:44.057 --> 14:45.536
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

15:03.250 --> 15:04.425
-MITCH, WHAT ARE
YOU DOING HERE?

15:05.600 --> 15:06.775
-I WORK HERE.

15:06.906 --> 15:07.732
-SHAUNI: WELL,
WHO'S WITH HOBIE?

15:08.690 --> 15:10.605
-THEY'RE KEEPING HIM IN THE
HOSPITAL FOR OBSERVATION.

15:10.735 --> 15:11.954
-IS HE GONNA BE OKAY?

15:12.650 --> 15:13.608
-YEAH, HE'S HANGING IN THERE.

15:14.609 --> 15:15.784
WHAT A LONG NIGHT.

15:16.916 --> 15:19.092
-WELL, DID THEY CONFIRM
IT WAS CHEMICAL POISONING?

15:19.222 --> 15:21.921
-YEAH, BUT HIS SYSTEM
DIDN'T ABSORB ENOUGH

15:22.051 --> 15:23.792
TO DETERMINE
THE EXACT COMPOUND.

15:24.575 --> 15:25.968
DID YOU GET THOSE WATER
SAMPLES FROM THE LAGOON?

15:26.621 --> 15:28.014
-WE WERE THERE AT
THE CRACK OF DAWN.

15:28.144 --> 15:29.624
LANE'S AT THE LAB RIGHT
NOW HAVING IT ANALYZED.

15:30.277 --> 15:31.843
-WHEN DO WE GET THE RESULTS?

15:31.974 --> 15:33.933
-I DON'T KNOW, BUT I'M
SURE IT'S GONNA BE AWHILE.

15:34.063 --> 15:35.673
LOOK, WHY DON'T YOU GO
HOME AND GET SOME SLEEP.

15:37.153 --> 15:38.502
-[SIGHS] I'M NOT TIRED.

15:38.633 --> 15:40.113
THEY PUT A COT IN
HOBIE'S ROOM FOR ME.

15:41.766 --> 15:43.420
DO YOU KNOW HE KEPT WAKING
UP IN THE MIDDLE OF THE NIGHT

15:43.551 --> 15:45.031
CRYING OUT FOR MOMMY?

15:45.596 --> 15:47.033
-ALL BOYS WANT THEIR
MOMMY WHEN THEY'RE SICK.

15:47.729 --> 15:49.470
-I KNOW BUT WHEN YOUR
SON IS LYING THERE IN PAIN

15:49.600 --> 15:51.428
AND THERE'S NOT A DAMN
THING YOU CAN DO ABOUT IT...

15:54.257 --> 15:55.867
I NEVER FELT SO HELPLESS
IN MY WHOLE LIFE.

15:56.520 --> 15:58.958
[SEAGULLS CAWING]

16:00.785 --> 16:06.704
ALRIGHT, PUT EDDIE ON 15,
MIMI ON 16, SHAUNI ON 17.

16:08.532 --> 16:09.490
DO YOU WANT TO
WORK AT HEADQUARTERS TODAY?

16:09.620 --> 16:11.448
-I'LL DO THAT THEN, NO PROBLEM.

16:11.579 --> 16:13.450
WHY DON'T YOU GET
SOME REST, YOU LOOK TIRED.

16:13.581 --> 16:16.671
-MITCH: YEAH, AND
AS FAR AS ONE AND TWO,

16:16.801 --> 16:18.368
PUT JIMMY AND BOBBY ON THOSE.

16:18.499 --> 16:19.935
-BEN: OKAY, I'LL DO THAT,
YOU TAKE CARE, ALRIGHT?

16:20.066 --> 16:21.458
HEY, WHAT'S HAPPENING, LANE?

16:21.589 --> 16:22.938
-HEY, HOW ARE YOU
DOING, GOOD TO SEE YA.

16:24.374 --> 16:25.506
-SO WHAT'D YOU FIND OUT?

16:26.115 --> 16:27.595
-ENOUGH TO LET ME
TAKE HIM HOME TONIGHT.

16:28.683 --> 16:30.206
-YOU KNOW, MITCH, HE'S
NOT OUT OF THE WOODS YET.

16:30.337 --> 16:32.034
